  FORMAT [Dn:]

This command formats a disk and
installs BW-DOS. Formatting must be
done first when preparing a new disk.

The drive number you specify is used
only to locate the DOS files, not to
choose which drive will be formatted.

The program will request the needed
information and then format the disk.
It cannot be controlled from a batch
file. Ramdisks cannot be formatted
with this command.

In addition to the four standard
formats - single, medium, double, and
double sided - three more options are
available.

Reset File System: Clears the disk.
The disk must already be formatted
and initialized with the SpartaDOS
file system. This is the fastest way
to clear a previously used disk.

Create File System: Initializes the
SpartaDOS file system. The disk must
already be physically formatted, and
the drive must support the Percom
configuration block. This option is
used for initializing hard disks.

Custom Configuration: Formats and
initializes the disk using freely
selectable parameters. The drive must
support the Percom configuration
block. This is used for special
formats supported by devices like
ATR8000, HDI, XF551 with 3.5" upgrade,
or the 1050 Mini.
